{
  "updated_summary": "The Intel Extreme Masters Chengdu 2024 Group Stage Advancement Match on Inferno saw G2 Esports and Team Liquid locked in a fierce battle, with G2 ultimately securing a 13-11 victory. Early rounds on Inferno showcased Team Liquid's strong offensive push, with players like NAF, YEKINDAR, and Twistzz making aggressive plays towards B-site, often met by G2's coordinated defense led by Nexa, huNter-, and m0NESY. Despite Team Liquid establishing an early lead, G2 consistently fought back, often through clutch plays from m0NESY and huNter-. Key moments included m0NESY's impressive 1v1 clutches denying sneaky defuses and securing rounds for G2, while Nexa's dual-wielded pistol eliminations proved critical. The commentators highlighted G2's resilience, noting their ability to "flip the script" and "chain some rounds together" after falling behind. The match was punctuated by intense firefights, precise sniper shots, and strategic utility usage, with sounds of gunshots, explosions, and UI alerts forming a constant backdrop. Real-world footage showed G2 players celebrating hard-fought round wins with fist pumps and cheers, contrasting with the visible disappointment of the Team Liquid coach. Sponsor logos from Intel, DHL, Predator, Qiddiya, Monster Energy, Logitech, Coinbase, and Honda were prominently displayed throughout the broadcast, underscoring the high-stakes professional esports environment."
}
